\date{2025-03-04}
\title{Split Idempotent}
\taxon{definition}

\import{stt-macros}

\p{Given an endomorphism #{p : X \to X} in a category #{\CC}, we say that it is a split idempotent if:

\ul{
\li{There exists a retract 
of #{X} - that is a triple #{(Y : \CC) \times (r : X \to Y) \times (s : Y \to X)} such that #{r \circ s = \id_Y}}

\li{The composition, #{s \circ r} is equal to #{p}}
}

}

